pullRequest.title: Fix pants version parsing
pullRequest.bodyText:
Problem
Internally at Twitter, we append some extra information to the pants version number. However, this means that the pants version parser doesn't work when trying to parse stable releases (1.20.0 as opposed to something like 1.20.0rc1)
Solution
Create a proper model for a PantsVersion, and use a validated regex to parse it.
TODO:

 Add tests for parsing: The test is already there (com.twitter.intellij.pants.util.PantsUtilTest#testIsCompatibleVersion)
 Integrate the new class more. This is the last commit. Since we read the version from a file, there aren't any real fields to update.

afterCommit.message: Change isCompatiblePantsVersion to use the new class instead

nodes.bodyText: I might also add a test for a version like 1.24.0rc1-git2481dab2-md59a1c1708 as well, since we see that in our internal pants repo. I am pretty sure that the parsing mechanism you've developed here is only going to capture the relevant numbers, but in the case that we modify the parsing in the future, it might be good to have a complete example?
Good change!! Thank you for fixing up naming hygiene here!
Btw, fantastic move to link to regex101.com -- thanks for thinking about this! This is exactly how we make regex a little more comprehensible.
Is there a reason we're using Pattern.MULTILINE here? I believe that would convert the above ^ into start-of-line instead of start-of-input, see: https://stackoverflow.com/a/6143347/2518889.
